<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: How do we add .bin Famitracker music into our prg code?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10127&amp;p=112618#p112618"><![CDATA[
If LOAD is $A896 why do you have &quot;.org $A916&quot;? And what is &quot;jsr $A916 + $0A&quot;? Also, doesn't .org only set the program counter? You need to place the data at that location, not just set the program counter.<br /><br />Also, your vblank NMI will never be called unless you turn it on. You want to jsr to INIT and then turn it on by writing to $2000 (see <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/PPU_registers" class="postlink">PPU registers</a>).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5165">rainwarrior</a> — Fri May 31, 2013 8:02 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
